The paper deals with information theory and signal processing, specifically the causal information rate-distortion function for stationary sources. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.ITP (Information Theory and Probability) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some statistical analysis and machine learning concepts, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions the Gaussian quadratic case, which could suggest a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia).
